laboratory_examinations.findings: Initial ultrasound at 13 weeks 2 days gestation showed thickened NT of 3.4 mm, absence of nasal bones, and poor ossifications in the cranium and vertebrae.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up ultrasound at 21 weeks 4 days showed mild improvement in cranium ossification with hypo-mineralization, persistent lack of nasal bones, poorly ossified vertebrae, femur and humerus length below the tenth percentile, and bowing of the tibia and fibula.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Identified a frame shift deletion in RUNX2 on chromosome 6p21.
